WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:12.940 --> 00:00:14.670
Inherited will...

3
00:00:14.670 --> 00:00:17.580
the tides of time,
and humanity's dreams...

4
00:00:17.580 --> 00:00:20.410
They cannot be stopped.

5
00:00:20.410 --> 00:00:23.520
As long as people seek freedom,

6
00:00:23.520 --> 00:00:26.150
these things will never cease to be.

7
00:00:34.860 --> 00:00:41.080
I only believe in the future -- I don't care if anyone laughs

8
00:00:41.120 --> 00:00:46.600
That racing passion makes you shine

9
00:00:46.620 --> 00:00:52.140
It's too bright, but I want to gaze at it

10
00:00:52.480 --> 00:00:56.120
I sense "aesthetics" somewhere

11
00:00:59.480 --> 00:01:02.740
I follow, follow in the footsteps

12
00:01:02.740 --> 00:01:06.030
of a dream that resembles no one

13
00:01:06.030 --> 00:01:09.260
Until I dramatically get it

14
00:01:18.120 --> 00:01:21.160
I'm going to catch, catch the shape

15
00:01:21.260 --> 00:01:24.240
of a dream no one can see

16
00:01:24.520 --> 00:01:30.260
I'm going to go with you, so passionate feelings

17
00:01:30.500 --> 00:01:33.620
I don't really need everything to add up

18
00:01:33.600 --> 00:01:36.790
Rather than run-of-the-mill daily life,

19
00:01:36.800 --> 00:01:40.390
run for paradise instead

20
00:01:49.960 --> 00:01:55.260
<b>Reverse Mountain</b>

21
00:02:08.480 --> 00:02:10.070
What's wrong, Zoro?

22
00:02:10.070 --> 00:02:12.570
You've had a serious look
on your face for a while.

23
00:02:12.570 --> 00:02:15.110
Well, I might just be
imagining things, but...

24
00:02:15.110 --> 00:02:16.070
But what?

25
00:02:16.070 --> 00:02:20.700
I feel like the ship
hasn't moved in a while.

26
00:02:24.960 --> 00:02:25.540
What?

27
00:02:26.630 --> 00:02:30.920
Now that you mention it,
the sail isn't catching any wind...

28
00:02:34.340 --> 00:02:35.470
Oh no...!

29
00:02:35.470 --> 00:02:37.550
We've entered the Calm Belt!

30
00:02:37.890 --> 00:02:38.890
The Balm Belt?

31
00:02:38.890 --> 00:02:39.720
The heck is that?

32
00:02:39.720 --> 00:02:42.230
The Calm Belt! A sea where
nothing moves a muscle!

33
00:02:42.230 --> 00:02:43.310
You grew some muscle?

34
00:02:43.310 --> 00:02:44.520
No, you idiot!

35
00:02:51.400 --> 00:02:52.610
Was that an earthquake?

36
00:02:52.610 --> 00:02:54.400
An earthquake? But we're at sea.

37
00:02:54.400 --> 00:02:56.820
Come on, guys, focus!

38
00:02:56.820 --> 00:02:58.740
Hoist the sails and start paddling!

39
00:02:58.740 --> 00:03:00.330
Put the ship back on course, now!

40
00:03:00.330 --> 00:03:01.700
As you wish, Nami!

41
00:03:02.040 --> 00:03:03.790
What are you panicking about?

42
00:03:03.790 --> 00:03:05.540
And why paddle? This is a sailboat.

43
00:03:05.540 --> 00:03:06.750
Yeah, why?

44
00:03:06.750 --> 00:03:09.590
Why bother when
the Marines are back there?

45
00:03:09.590 --> 00:03:12.710
Just shut up and do as I say!
We're in big trouble!

46
00:03:12.710 --> 00:03:14.550
But the sea is nice and quiet here.

47
00:03:14.550 --> 00:03:15.170
Yeah.

48
00:03:15.170 --> 00:03:17.930
Alright, fine! I'll explain!

49
00:03:17.930 --> 00:03:23.350
Listen. Since we were in such a hurry,
we went farther south than intended!

50
00:03:23.350 --> 00:03:25.230
So we're in the Grand Line now?

51
00:03:25.230 --> 00:03:27.020
Alright!

52
00:03:27.020 --> 00:03:29.860
If it was that easy,
anyone could enter!

53
00:03:31.440 --> 00:03:32.440
Look here.

54
00:03:32.440 --> 00:03:37.410
The Grand Line runs between
these two strips of sea.

55
00:03:37.410 --> 00:03:42.240
Are you following? The two strips
are called the Calm Belts.

56
00:03:43.330 --> 00:03:47.580
The reason's unknown, but no wind
or currents flow through them.

57
00:03:47.580 --> 00:03:49.630
These seas are completely calm.

58
00:03:49.630 --> 00:03:52.380
Sailboats need wind to move
so it's very dangerous—

59
00:03:52.380 --> 00:03:54.130
maybe even fatal—without it!

60
00:03:54.130 --> 00:03:55.630
Did you get all that, Luffy?

61
00:03:55.630 --> 00:03:57.720
Yeah. Basically, we're in trouble.

62
00:03:57.720 --> 00:04:00.180
I see. Good, you got
more than I thought.

63
00:04:00.180 --> 00:04:03.140
So that's why the geezer
said it was dangerous...

64
00:04:03.140 --> 00:04:05.850
That explains the lack of wind.

65
00:04:05.850 --> 00:04:08.190
Not much we can do
if the ship can't move.

66
00:04:08.190 --> 00:04:09.940
Can't we just wait for wind to–

67
00:04:09.940 --> 00:04:14.070
I just explained this! Wind won't blow
no matter how long you wait here!

68
00:04:14.070 --> 00:04:15.230
And that's not all!

69
00:04:15.230 --> 00:04:18.610
There's another reason
this area is dangerous!

70
00:04:18.610 --> 00:04:20.030
The Calm Belt is–

71
00:04:22.030 --> 00:04:23.660
What's going on?

72
00:04:28.870 --> 00:04:31.170
They're huge!

73
00:04:36.920 --> 00:04:39.590
The Calm Belt is a nest of sea kings.

74
00:04:39.590 --> 00:04:41.550
Specifically colossal ones.

75
00:04:41.930 --> 00:04:46.020
They're the other reason people
can't cross the Calm Belt...

76
00:04:47.020 --> 00:04:48.940
What do we do now?

77
00:04:49.350 --> 00:04:51.480
They'll go back into
the sea eventually.

78
00:04:51.480 --> 00:04:54.860
When they do, we paddle
as hard as possible.

79
00:04:54.860 --> 00:04:56.610
Are you serious?!

80
00:04:56.610 --> 00:04:57.490
Shut it, idiot!

81
00:04:59.240 --> 00:05:01.070
Sorry...

82
00:05:05.490 --> 00:05:07.160
Hold on a sec...!

83
00:05:07.160 --> 00:05:08.620
If it does that...

84
00:05:08.620 --> 00:05:11.120
He's gonna sneeze!

85
00:05:11.750 --> 00:05:14.000
– What?!
– What?!

86
00:05:14.000 --> 00:05:16.750
Wow! It feels like we're flying!

87
00:05:18.670 --> 00:05:25.140
We are flying!

88
00:05:27.560 --> 00:05:30.350
Looks like we're back on course...

89
00:05:30.350 --> 00:05:33.900
We should be seeing
the Red Line any moment now.

90
00:05:37.900 --> 00:05:40.950
Are we finally going
into the Grand Line?!

91
00:05:41.780 --> 00:05:46.030
Hey, Sanji! We're here,
we're here, we're finally here!

92
00:05:46.030 --> 00:05:47.620
That hurts!

93
00:05:47.620 --> 00:05:48.700
Sorry...

94
00:05:49.160 --> 00:05:50.410
Zoro!

95
00:05:50.410 --> 00:05:51.660
But...
We're here, we're here!

96
00:05:51.660 --> 00:05:55.290
We're here, we're here, we're here!
is the drawing an accurate
representation of what we'll find?

97
00:05:55.290 --> 00:05:57.420
Quit it!

98
00:06:03.050 --> 00:06:04.140
Look at this!

99
00:06:05.390 --> 00:06:09.060
I'd heard the rumors about it,
and it's drawn on this map, too!

100
00:06:09.060 --> 00:06:13.100
If all of that is true, then the entrance
to the Grand Line is a mountain!

101
00:06:13.100 --> 00:06:14.650
A mountain?

102
00:06:14.650 --> 00:06:16.020
We gotta crash into it?

103
00:06:16.020 --> 00:06:17.150
You're kidding, right?

104
00:06:17.150 --> 00:06:22.150
I doubted it myself, but the map
shows canals leading to the mountain.

105
00:06:22.150 --> 00:06:24.320
That might mean we have to go up it!

106
00:06:25.410 --> 00:06:27.200
Cool!

107
00:06:27.200 --> 00:06:28.660
What are you talking about?!

108
00:06:28.660 --> 00:06:33.040
Even with canals or whatever,
a ship can't climb up a mountain!

109
00:06:33.040 --> 00:06:34.670
But that's what the map says!

110
00:06:34.670 --> 00:06:38.130
Exactly! Nami would never
say anything wrong!

111
00:06:38.750 --> 00:06:41.380
You stole that map
from Buggy, right?

112
00:06:41.380 --> 00:06:42.800
Can we really trust it?

113
00:06:42.800 --> 00:06:44.090
H-Hey!

114
00:06:44.090 --> 00:06:46.140
Someone help me move the whipstaff!

115
00:06:46.140 --> 00:06:48.510
Sanji! Give Usopp a hand!

116
00:06:46.720 --> 00:06:49.510
It won't budge!

117
00:06:48.510 --> 00:06:50.850
I can't think with all his shouting!

118
00:06:49.510 --> 00:06:52.390
It won't move! Someone help!

119
00:06:50.850 --> 00:06:52.390
Right away, Nami!

120
00:06:52.390 --> 00:06:53.480
Here I go!

121
00:06:53.940 --> 00:06:57.400
D-Doesn't this current
seem a bit strong?!

122
00:06:57.400 --> 00:06:58.150
Huh?

123
00:06:58.150 --> 00:06:59.770
Usopp, say that again!

124
00:06:59.770 --> 00:07:02.530
"D-Doesn't this current
seem a bit strong?!"

125
00:07:02.530 --> 00:07:04.320
Current...

126
00:07:04.320 --> 00:07:05.150
That's it!

127
00:07:05.150 --> 00:07:06.280
What's it?

128
00:07:06.280 --> 00:07:08.120
The canals do go up the mountain!

129
00:07:08.120 --> 00:07:10.660
You're still on that?

130
00:07:10.660 --> 00:07:11.370
Look here!

131
00:07:11.370 --> 00:07:12.500
See?

132
00:07:12.500 --> 00:07:15.710
The guiding light was
definitely pointing to here.

133
00:07:15.710 --> 00:07:18.040
Right on the Red Line:
Reverse Mountain!

134
00:07:18.040 --> 00:07:20.500
Hey! What do I do now?!

135
00:07:21.050 --> 00:07:23.170
See these canals here?

136
00:07:23.170 --> 00:07:28.640
If major currents from the four seas
all flowed toward this mountain...

137
00:07:29.970 --> 00:07:34.230
Then the four currents would go up
these canals, collide at the top,

138
00:07:34.230 --> 00:07:36.310
and flow into the Grand Line!

139
00:07:36.850 --> 00:07:39.020
Reverse Mountain is a winter island,

140
00:07:39.020 --> 00:07:44.360
so any currents that collide with
the Red Line will go into the depths.

141
00:07:44.360 --> 00:07:46.990
If we screw up and miss
the entrance to the canal...

142
00:07:47.610 --> 00:07:50.450
the Going Merry will crash
into the Red Line...

143
00:07:52.700 --> 00:07:54.870
and get completely wrecked!

144
00:07:55.580 --> 00:07:58.250
Then we'd end up at the bottom
of the ocean. Get it?

145
00:07:58.250 --> 00:07:59.670
Oh, very interesting!

146
00:07:59.670 --> 00:08:02.710
So, basically, it's a mystery mountain!

147
00:08:04.090 --> 00:08:07.010
Well, I guess you wouldn't...

148
00:08:07.630 --> 00:08:10.640
All in all, now that
we're on this current,

149
00:08:10.640 --> 00:08:12.390
as long as we steer correctly,

150
00:08:12.390 --> 00:08:15.600
it's a straight shot to the summit
of Reverse Mountain!

151
00:08:15.930 --> 00:08:18.060
You're amazing, Nami!

152
00:08:18.060 --> 00:08:20.980
I've never heard of someone
going up a mountain by boat.

153
00:08:20.980 --> 00:08:22.690
I've heard some stories!

154
00:08:23.070 --> 00:08:24.480
About the mystery mountain?

155
00:08:24.820 --> 00:08:25.690
No.

156
00:08:25.690 --> 00:08:30.700
I heard that half of everyone who heads
to the Grand Line die before entering...

157
00:08:31.780 --> 00:08:34.740
I knew getting in wouldn't be easy.

158
00:08:35.120 --> 00:08:36.620
Sanji! Could you get the sail?

159
00:08:36.620 --> 00:08:38.370
Of course, Nami!

160
00:08:38.370 --> 00:08:39.500
Luffy! Help out!

161
00:08:39.500 --> 00:08:41.460
What?!

162
00:08:51.970 --> 00:08:53.220
Hey!

163
00:08:53.220 --> 00:08:55.350
I see the mystery mountain!

164
00:08:55.350 --> 00:08:56.970
– Wh-What?!
– What?!

165
00:08:57.390 --> 00:09:00.020
Th-That's insanely huge!

166
00:09:02.400 --> 00:09:04.980
So that's the Red Line, huh?!

167
00:09:05.480 --> 00:09:11.490
Th-Th-The t-top's all the way
above the clouds!

168
00:09:31.930 --> 00:09:33.720
We're getting sucked in!

169
00:09:34.350 --> 00:09:35.970
Hold the rudder tight!

170
00:09:35.970 --> 00:09:37.470
– On it!
– On it!

171
00:09:44.770 --> 00:09:47.360
N-Nami! Wh-Where's the entrance?!

172
00:09:47.360 --> 00:09:50.320
We're gonna crash
if we keep going this way!

173
00:09:52.660 --> 00:09:54.570
The crack in that cliff...

174
00:09:57.450 --> 00:10:00.290
Nami! What do we do?!

175
00:10:00.290 --> 00:10:01.710
Keep going straight ahead!

176
00:10:01.710 --> 00:10:02.870
Are you sure?!

177
00:10:02.870 --> 00:10:04.080
Just do it!

178
00:10:05.080 --> 00:10:07.040
Nami! Is that the entrance?

179
00:10:07.040 --> 00:10:08.500
Most likely!

180
00:10:09.170 --> 00:10:10.970
I can't believe this...!

181
00:10:11.630 --> 00:10:15.140
The damn ocean really is
flowing up the mountain!

182
00:10:20.220 --> 00:10:23.480
We gotta be careful sailing
through those gates!

183
00:10:23.810 --> 00:10:26.360
If we don't get it just right,
the ship is done for!

184
00:10:30.150 --> 00:10:33.360
W-We're a little off!
More to the right! The right!

185
00:10:33.360 --> 00:10:35.660
The right?! Go starboard!

186
00:10:38.450 --> 00:10:40.950
C-Come on, now!

187
00:10:47.880 --> 00:10:49.420
– The whipstaff!
– The whipstaff!

188
00:10:49.420 --> 00:10:52.130
Gum-Gum Balloon!

189
00:11:00.760 --> 00:11:02.310
Luffy!

190
00:11:02.310 --> 00:11:03.180
Grab on!

191
00:11:16.070 --> 00:11:18.740
– We made it!
– We made it!

192
00:11:24.870 --> 00:11:28.210
Now it's just a straight
shot to the summit!

193
00:11:32.460 --> 00:11:35.220
A-Awesome!

194
00:11:42.470 --> 00:11:43.560
Awesome, right?

195
00:11:45.640 --> 00:11:48.440
We're in the clouds!

196
00:11:59.370 --> 00:12:01.700
So cool!

197
00:12:03.120 --> 00:12:05.200
Now we're above the clouds!

198
00:12:15.550 --> 00:12:18.630
Look! It's the summit! The summit!

199
00:12:31.400 --> 00:12:33.650
Yahoo!

200
00:12:54.750 --> 00:12:55.800
I see it!

201
00:12:56.210 --> 00:12:58.630
This is the greatest sea in the world!

202
00:12:58.630 --> 00:12:59.930
The Grand Line!

203
00:13:02.640 --> 00:13:06.970
The One Piece is somewhere up ahead!

204
00:13:07.560 --> 00:13:10.100
Go!

205
00:13:24.620 --> 00:13:26.490
Did you hear that just now?

206
00:13:26.490 --> 00:13:28.410
Wasn't it just the wind?

207
00:13:28.410 --> 00:13:31.580
It must be from all the weird
landforms around here.

208
00:13:36.250 --> 00:13:37.210
What's that?

209
00:13:37.800 --> 00:13:40.300
Nami! I see a mountain up ahead!

210
00:13:40.300 --> 00:13:42.630
A mountain?! That can't be right!

211
00:13:42.630 --> 00:13:44.680
But there's really one there!

212
00:13:44.680 --> 00:13:46.970
Who cares?! Go!

213
00:13:47.640 --> 00:13:51.640
It should be open sea once
we pass the Twin Capes up ahead!

214
00:13:57.480 --> 00:13:58.860
Oh, crap!

215
00:14:01.030 --> 00:14:02.490
It's not a mountain!

216
00:14:02.490 --> 00:14:03.740
It's a big black wall!

217
00:14:03.740 --> 00:14:04.910
No, it's not! That's...

218
00:14:04.910 --> 00:14:06.030
What is it then?!

219
00:14:06.030 --> 00:14:07.280
I-I-I-It's...

220
00:14:07.280 --> 00:14:09.410
It's a whale!

221
00:14:11.910 --> 00:14:13.420
Wh-Wh-What are we g-gonna do?!

222
00:14:13.420 --> 00:14:14.380
We should fight it!

223
00:14:14.380 --> 00:14:16.540
Are you crazy?! How are
we gonna fight that?!

224
00:14:16.540 --> 00:14:19.510
B-B-But, i-i-it's blocking our way!

225
00:14:19.510 --> 00:14:21.220
What are we gonna do?!

226
00:14:21.220 --> 00:14:22.670
Hold on a sec!

227
00:14:23.220 --> 00:14:27.180
If it looks like a wall from
this close, where are its eyes?!

228
00:14:27.680 --> 00:14:31.310
That's right! Maybe it
hasn't noticed us yet!

229
00:14:31.310 --> 00:14:33.850
Either way, we're about
to crash into it!

230
00:14:33.850 --> 00:14:35.900
Hey! There's an opening on the left!

231
00:14:35.900 --> 00:14:38.360
Port! Hard to port!

232
00:14:38.940 --> 00:14:40.440
But the whipstaff is broken!

233
00:14:40.440 --> 00:14:42.900
Well, figure something out! I'll help!

234
00:14:42.900 --> 00:14:44.280
Oh, yeah!

235
00:14:44.280 --> 00:14:46.570
I've got an idea!

236
00:14:46.570 --> 00:14:47.240
Luffy...?

237
00:14:47.240 --> 00:14:49.120
Hey, what are you doing?!

238
00:14:54.460 --> 00:14:56.290
This isn't working!

239
00:14:56.290 --> 00:14:58.880
The ship won't turn!

240
00:14:58.880 --> 00:15:00.170
Dammit!

241
00:15:00.170 --> 00:15:02.300
Don't give up!

242
00:15:10.970 --> 00:15:12.890
Is this it...?!

243
00:15:19.900 --> 00:15:22.110
The cannon?!

244
00:15:22.110 --> 00:15:24.070
Alright! Did it stop?

245
00:15:32.080 --> 00:15:33.160
We're screwed...

246
00:15:33.580 --> 00:15:34.580
Yeah, this is it...

247
00:15:37.420 --> 00:15:39.330
My special seat!

248
00:15:56.390 --> 00:15:56.980
Let's...

249
00:15:56.980 --> 00:15:58.900
Let's book it while we still can!

250
00:15:58.900 --> 00:16:00.900
What the heck is going on?!

251
00:16:00.900 --> 00:16:03.400
Is it so big that
it didn't even feel it?!

252
00:16:03.400 --> 00:16:04.740
Or is it just slow?!

253
00:16:04.740 --> 00:16:06.700
Who cares?! Let's get
the hell out of here!

254
00:16:12.530 --> 00:16:13.580
My ears!

255
00:16:13.580 --> 00:16:15.200
Paddle! Just keep paddling!

256
00:16:15.200 --> 00:16:17.120
We have to get away from it!

257
00:16:23.340 --> 00:16:24.460
Luffy...?

258
00:16:24.460 --> 00:16:25.840
You!

259
00:16:25.840 --> 00:16:30.430
What the hell did you do
to my special seat?!

260
00:16:31.720 --> 00:16:34.720
– You dumbass!
– You dumbass!

261
00:16:41.650 --> 00:16:44.480
How was that, huh?!
Bring it on, you bastard!

262
00:16:44.480 --> 00:16:46.070
– Shut up already, you idiot!
– Shut up already, you idiot!

263
00:16:50.070 --> 00:16:51.450
Wh-What?

264
00:17:07.380 --> 00:17:09.220
Luffy!

265
00:17:15.430 --> 00:17:18.390
I'm not gonna die!

266
00:17:43.500 --> 00:17:44.840
What am I gonna do?

267
00:17:44.840 --> 00:17:46.380
They all got eaten...

268
00:17:47.420 --> 00:17:50.380
Hey, you! Spit them out!
Give everyone back!

269
00:17:50.380 --> 00:17:52.300
Spit them out already! Listen to me!

270
00:17:52.300 --> 00:17:53.220
You–

271
00:17:55.470 --> 00:17:57.220
You... You jerk!

272
00:17:57.640 --> 00:17:59.730
Are you diving?! Stop it!

273
00:17:59.730 --> 00:18:02.190
Hey! I said stop! Hey!

274
00:18:02.980 --> 00:18:05.150
Please, stop! Give my friends back!

275
00:18:05.610 --> 00:18:06.400
Hey!

276
00:18:06.400 --> 00:18:08.110
Stop it already!

277
00:18:08.480 --> 00:18:10.780
We were just about
to go on an adventure!

278
00:18:10.780 --> 00:18:12.110
I can't lose them!

279
00:18:12.610 --> 00:18:15.240
Give them back!

280
00:18:36.760 --> 00:18:38.850
So, what do you think?

281
00:18:38.850 --> 00:18:40.770
What do I think...?

282
00:18:40.770 --> 00:18:42.480
What should I think?

283
00:18:42.480 --> 00:18:44.230
H-H-H-H-How...?

284
00:18:44.230 --> 00:18:48.400
We were definitely
swallowed by that whale...

285
00:18:50.150 --> 00:18:51.820
Is this a dream?

286
00:18:51.820 --> 00:18:54.400
Yeah, it's gotta be a dream.

287
00:19:00.080 --> 00:19:02.620
Then, how do you explain
that island and house?

288
00:19:02.620 --> 00:19:04.000
Hallucinations.

289
00:19:08.590 --> 00:19:10.750
So, that's also...?

290
00:19:11.420 --> 00:19:14.760
– It's an imperial squid!
– It's an imperial squid!

291
00:19:35.990 --> 00:19:37.990
Looks like someone lives there.

292
00:19:37.990 --> 00:19:39.570
Let's hope they're human.

293
00:19:40.580 --> 00:19:42.580
I've had enough. I wanna go home.

294
00:19:42.580 --> 00:19:46.370
Luffy's gone, too...
What's gonna happen to us?

295
00:19:46.370 --> 00:19:48.040
You're right! Where's Luffy?!

296
00:19:50.090 --> 00:19:51.920
What the heck is all this?

297
00:19:51.920 --> 00:19:55.840
Why is there a door
to a hallway inside a whale?

298
00:19:58.720 --> 00:19:59.800
A ship...

299
00:19:59.800 --> 00:20:03.970
Sh-Sh-Should we f-fire
the cannon at that island?!

300
00:20:03.970 --> 00:20:05.810
No, hold on a sec...

301
00:20:07.270 --> 00:20:09.270
Someone's coming out...
